                            <comment id="17478211" author="houston" created="Tue, 18 Jan 2022 21:13:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The test fails, because it expects that the replica for shard 1 that gets created at the end will always be called: &lt;tt&gt;halfcollection_shard1_replica_n1&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However sometimes the replica for shard 2 is called &quot;halfcollection_shard2_replica_n1&quot; and the replica for shard 1 is called &quot;halfcollection_shard1_replica_n2&quot;, resulting in the test failing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is no reason to create 2 shards in the end anyways, 1 shard is enough to cause the test to fail reliably.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17478235" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 18 Jan 2022 22:06:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 3eefabbf1caf740ee802b2002a834dd1bb6e34f2 in solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/main from Houston Putman&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=3eefabb&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=3eefabb&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15935&quot; title=&quot;CollectionsAPIDistributedZkTest.testCreateShouldFailOnExistingCore fails consistently&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-15935&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-15935&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Fix CollectionsAPIDistributedZkTest.testCreateShouldFailOnExistingCore (#539)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The test fails because it expects that the replica for shard 1 that gets created at the end will always be called &quot;halfcollection_shard1_replica_n1&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However sometimes the replica for shard 2 is called &quot;halfcollection_shard2_replica_n1&quot; and the replica for shard 1 is called &quot;halfcollection_shard1_replica_n2&quot;, resulting in the test failing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is no reason to create 2 shards in the end anyways, 1 shard is enough to cause the test to fail reliably.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
